Knut secretary general Wilson Sossion (pictured) is hopeful the government will honour the Sh54 billion pledge made to teachers. &ldquo;In the next four years teachers will not go to the streets to demand pay,&rdquo; he said. Sossion said the government should now hire more teachers to end the shortage. He spoke during the opening of Lorraine Girls High School in Letin, Bureti constituency, on Friday.